      <div class="msgContentFrame"><li><u>The Thaumaturge Guide</u></li> <br />-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br /> <br /><b>Introduction</b> <br />-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br />I started creating this guide many months ago. I have put together all my knowledge of a job that for some reason I was strangely drawn to right from the start. I have spent much time playing the class of Thaumaturge (THM) and hope that when you read this guide you will get some useful information that helps you in your quest for fun and excitement. I don't claim to know everything, but anything I put in the guide is from personal observation unless stated otherwise. If you have any feedback it would be greatly appreciated and of course if you can add to it please post so I can credit you and add the information. If I can validate the information before I put it in then I will, otherwise I will state that it is so far unconfirmed by myself. <br /> <br />---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br /> <br /><b>Contents:</b> <br /> <br />In this guide you will find: <br /> <br />1. Thaumaturge what is it? <br />2. Beginning the game as a THM <br />3. The THM Guild and Guildmarks <br />4. THM Abilities list (All abilities in orange are confirmed) <br />5. THM Equipment &amp; Weapons list <br />6. Spell Combinations <br />7. Solo Hunting Grounds <br />a) La Noscea <br />b) Thanalan <br />c) The Black Shroud <br />8. Stats <br />9. Macros <br />10. Soloist vs Party Mage <br />11. Testing <br />12. Credits <br /> <br />*** Warning - This guide may contain some spoilers - Warning *** <br /> <br />---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br />UPDATED 8/12/2010 <br />---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br />1. Thaumaturge, what is it? <br /> <br />Disciple of Magic: Thaumaturge. <br /> <br />“Death is only the beginning.  <br />In the hands of a skilled practitioner, thaumaturgy can be a force of terrifying destruction. At the heart of this school of magic lies the ability to call forth and command the latent aether within oneself through deep introspection. <br />To then mold that aether into sorcery, the thaumaturge makes use of a scepter or staff, within which is housed a medium -- a natural stone imbued with magical properties. The guild is centered at the Arrzaneth Ossuary in Ul'dah, within those hallowed halls are said to reside powers of life, death, and the beyond.” <br /> <br />Role: <br />“Thaumaturges are unparalleled in their powers of destruction, eclipsing even the Disciple of War. <br />By enfeebling enemies and enhancing allies, thaumaturgy can prove to be an invaluable asset, particularly in battles of attrition.” <br />For further information on this relating to the real world check out this link <a href="HTTP://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thaumaturgy" rel="external nofollow" title="en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thaumaturgy">here.</a> <br /> <br />Thaumaturge is a Debuffer, Healer, crowd controller and to a much lesser extent Nuker and Buffer. It is a difficult class to describe and having played one for many months now I still don’t have the words to truly encapsulate the class. If you pick the road of the THM and play it with gusto I predict that you will have to think on your toes quite often, think about where you and others stand, learn to love the macro and targeting system, but most of all enjoy a class that has some level of complexity compared to DOW jobs. <br /> <br />At present it is the least played job on most servers and there are many opinions why. Check out the forums for further information. :) <br />---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br /> <br />2. Beginning the game as a Thaumaturge. <br /> <br />I recommend that if you are reading this guide before you have created your character, you start out in the starting city of either Ul’dah or Limsa Lominsa, I tried both during the testing phase and went with Ul’Dah for retail as it had the Thaumaturge Guild there but also because it has the Goldsmithing Guild in it, Alchemist Guild and Miners guild – The Goldsmithing Guild is very useful to you as you may want to rank up this craft to make and repair your weapons as you go along your THM journey. I know I found this very useful. <br /> <br />Your starting gear is limited but proficient enough for you to get to Rank 10 with. You may want to purchase better gear as you make those first few ranks but if you play well you will get to Rank 10 very quickly and your purchases may soon become out of date. You will get Gil(the currency everyone uses to trade for items etc) if you complete regional levequests. This will give you the means to purchase new gear if you need. I stayed with my low level gear (Mostly all called Weathered 'insert name of item' etc) and my Onion Helm until about Rank 12 before I bought anything new. <br /> <br />Go out there and have fun – learn the job as it progresses. <br />---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br /> <br />3. The THM Guild and Guildmarks <br /> <br /><span style="color:indigo">Thaumaturges Guild</span> <br /> <br />The Guild is located in Ul’Dah and there is not much you can really do there until you are R20 apart from spend any Guildmarks you may have (more of this later but you may not get many of these for a while anyway) <br /> <br />Rank 20: <br />Your first guild quest can be taken at Rank 20 (unconfirmed by me, but supposedly as early as Rank 18) and you have to be at least at Mission 15 or above in the <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/quest.html?ffxivquest=110009" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/quest.html?ffxivquest=110009">main storyline.</a> <br /> <br />Name: The Big Payback <br />NPC quest starter: Yayake, Thaumaturge Guild, Ul'Dah <br />other NPC's: I'llofii(THM guild) <br />Mobs: <span class="spoiler" onmouseover="this.className=''" onmouseout="this.className='spoiler'">Three rounds of Goats (5+1+1)</span> <br />Finish NPC: I'llofii(THM guild) <br />Reward: <span class="spoiler" onmouseover="this.className=''" onmouseout="this.className='spoiler'">20k Gil, 2k Guildmarks</span> <br /><a href="HTTP://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9f7IzmZgiZw" rel="external nofollow" title="www.youtube.com/watch?v=9f7IzmZgiZw">Youtube Link</a>  <br /> <br />(thanks Obiar)**Finally completed this myself as a 21 THM - not too hard. The first wave are very very easy - hitting me for around 10-15 each, the next mob is on you very quickly (already before I had finished killing the other group), but again is pretty easy. The final mob appears after you get a drop so dont think the fight is done! This one is a little tricky so I would recommend saving punishing barbs for this fight, keep hp up and hit as often as you can with damnation (I found absorb def to be good in this fight).  <br /> <br />Rank 30: <br />Your second Guild quest is at Rank 30. You have to be Rank 30 to get this mission. <br /> <br />Name: Revalry and Rivalry <br />NPC quest starter: Yayake, Thaumaturge Guild, Ul'Dah <br />Other NPC's: Overweening Thaumaturge(THM guild), Baderon (Limsa Lominsa), Bodenoff (Limsa Lominsa) <br />Mobs: <span class="spoiler" onmouseover="this.className=''" onmouseout="this.className='spoiler'">Ignis Fatuss (Bomb)</span> <br />Finish NPC: Yayake(THM guild) <br />Reward: <span class="spoiler" onmouseover="this.className=''" onmouseout="this.className='spoiler'">30k Gil, 3k Guildmarks</span> <br /> <br />Walkthrough: <br /><span class="spoiler" onmouseover="this.className=''" onmouseout="this.className='spoiler'">1. When you have hit Rank 30 Thaumaturge. <br />2. Speak to Yayake in the Thaumaturges Guild in Ul'Dah. <br />3. Speak to Overweening Thaumaturge in the corner of the Thaumaturges Guild. <br />4. Head to Limsa Lominsa and speak with Badaron in the adventurers Guild. <br />5. Head out into La Nocsea and go north of Camp Bearded Rock (pos:20-26). <br />6. Enter the instance when promted and fight the Ignis Fatuss - was Blue to a Rank 30 - easy fight. <br />7. Head to Bodenoff at the Blacksmiths Guild in Limsa Lominsa. <br />8. Speak to him twice and choose to use the power of the echo. <br />9. Head back to Ul'Dah and speak once again with Yayake. <br />10. Speak once again with the Overweening Thaumaturge. <br />11. Speak one more time with Yayake for your reward. 30k Gil and 3k THM guildmarks.</span> <br />Complete! <br /> <br />Rank 36: <br /> <br />TBA <br /> <br /><span style="color:pink">THM Guildmarks</span>  <br /> <br />Guildmarks are awarded from leves. They replace the gil reward but sometimes you can still get an item reward in addition to guildmarks. If you can, trade completed leves for leves that give guildmarks as a reward, as you can double or treble the total amount of guildmarks you get. I have currently bought four traits with guildmarks as I have been only been awarded THM guildmarks as my other classes are below 10 and 20 respectively, but I have no more that I can buy until Shadowfall (which I bought for 500 in Beta lol!) because it is a R40 ability that probably won’t become available until I am much higher. <br /> <br /><i><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28589" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28589">Silouette</a></i> – [6000marks] - Single attack that reduces enmity for caster. I found this to be a great alternative to PD! No action cost, so you can equip as well as PD and when I was doing Leve’s each time I got hate I cast this and the mobs turned away! Wow such a cool move for us. It hits for nearly the same as PD so you can spam it as much as you like. I found it most useful when I needed to cure another player with Sacrifice II. I would cast Cure and then immediately cast Silhouette – PING no enmity. Just got this in retail but not had opportunity to use it in party situation yet. Hope it’s as good as in Beta. <br /> <br /><i><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28567" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28567">Shadowfall</a></i> - [12000marks] - Launch a shadowy attack, dealing damage to target and nearby enemies. Optimal Rank 40. I got this ability available to me at R33. This ability is an attack similar to Phantom Dart however it hits all mobs in a conal Aoe range at a similar distance to phantom dart. You have to be careful with this as it seems pretty powerful (hitting for more than Phantom Dart). Remember that a mob must be red before you will get any SP/EXP from it so ensure that the mobs you are killing are all red. I found this works very well for Leve's with mobs in a party. Another good aspect to this move is that it generates you lots of TP, so its useful for setting off Flashfreeze and Damnation. <br /> <br /><i><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=29477" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=29477">Firm Conviction</a></i> - Raises defence while casting. [8000 marks]. Please read my other information post on this <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1288877369159405438&amp;page=1" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1288877369159405438&amp;page=1">&gt;&gt;here</a>  <br /> <br /><i>Driven By Faith</i> - [8000] Converts an attribute point allocation of PIE+5 to VIT +5: Intended to be used on other Disciples of War to convert stats favourable to the Thaumaturge into stats more useful on other classes. <br /> <br /><i>Complete Control</i> - [8000] Converts an attribute point allocation of MND+5 to DEX+5: Intended to be used on other Disciples of War to convert stats favourable to the Thaumaturge into stats more useful on other classes. <br />***Warning*** Both Complete Control and Driven by Faith are not worth buying unless you plan to have a mele class that you can use these traits for. Yes these are not equipped when you are playing a THM so are totally worthless as far as I can tell. <br />---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br /> <br />4. Thaumaturge Abilities List: <br /> <br /> <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 1:</b></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=22302" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=22302">Phantom Dart</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28484" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28484">Exhaltation</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28590" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28590">Scourge</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28596" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28596">Banish</a>  <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 2:</b></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28055" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28055">Blood Rite</a> <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 4:</b></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28665" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28665">Sacrifice</a> <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 6:</b></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28617" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28617">Poison</a> <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 8:</b></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28629" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28629">Slow</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28631" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28631">Gravity</a> <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 10:</b></span>  <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28465" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28465">Punishing Barbs</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28564" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28564">Damnation</a> <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 12:</b></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28601" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28601">Bio</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28605" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28605">Dia</a> <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 14:</b></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28468" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28468">Dark Seal</a> <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 16:</b></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28670" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28670">Stygian Spikes</a> <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 18:</b></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28644" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28644">Absorb ATT</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28647" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28647">Absorb DEF</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28650" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28650">Absorb ACC</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28653" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28653">Absorb EVA</a> <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 20:</b></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28659" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28659">Siphon MP</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28667" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28667">Sacrifice II</a> <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 22:</b></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28472" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28472">Initiation</a> <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 24:</b></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28598" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28598">Banish II</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28593" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28593">Scourge II</a>  <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 26</b></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28609" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28609">Drain</a>  <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 28</b> </span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28633" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28633">Bind</a>  <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28637" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28637">Paralyze</a>  <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28635" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28635">Silence</a>  <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 30</b> </span>  <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28486" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28486">Flashfreeze</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28475" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28475">Paradigm Shift</a>  <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 32</b> </span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28662" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28662">Siphon TP</a>  <br /><span style="color:orange"><b>Rank 34</b> </span> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28463" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=28463">Blood Rite II</a>   <br /><b>Rank 36</b>  <br />Bio II  <br />Dia II  <br /><b>Rank 38</b> <br />Blind  <br /><b>Rank 40</b>  <br />Emulate  <br /><b>Rank 42</b> <br />Shadowsear  <br />Stygian Spikes II  <br /><b>Rank 44</b>  <br />Poison II  <br /><b>Rank 46</b>  <br />Dark Seal II  <br /><b>Rank 48</b>  <br />Drain II  <br />Sacrifice III  <br /><b>Rank 50</b>  <br />Contagion  <br />Numbing Rime II  <br />---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br />2. Equipment  <br /> <br />Here is a DoM Gear List that was accumulated by djocapn (ty also to xgaelx) <br /> <br />Head:  <br /> <br />Rank 6 - Hempen Hat (+18 MP)  <br />Rank 7 - Lauan Half Mask (+11 HP, +11 MP)  <br />Rank 10 - Hempen Sugarloaf Hat (+1 DEX, +1 MND)  <br />Rank 11 - Cotton Coif (+12 HP, +12 MP)  <br />Rank 12 - Copper Circlet (+12 MP)  <br />Rank 12 - Cotton Bandana (+1 VIT, +1 INT)  <br />Rank 17 - Willow Half Mask (+14 HP, +14 MP)  <br />Rank 20 - Cotton Sugarloaf Hat (