      <div class="msgContentFrame">No you dont need to confirm using the macro setup. <br /> <br />It takes one combined keypress of CTRL + &lt;number&gt;  <i>or</i> ALT + &lt;number&gt; <br /> <br />I have my aoe on/off macros set up as follows: <br /> <br /><u>ALT+1</u> <br />/aoe on <br /> <br /><u>ALT+2</u> <br />/aoe off <br /> <br />All it takes is one key press and each time the chat log lets me know that I have selected single target spellcasting or aoe. I do not have to press enter to do this. You will notice if you do this correctly that the green arrows beside the 'Area of effect' icon with either be there or be gone depending on what you have selected. <br /> <br />Make sure you have set up your macros correctly, so check your configuration. <br /> <br />Also any spell that targets a specific mob requires you to target mob, select spell which which creates a purple spinning circle around the target and then a key press to implement the spell (enter) or cancel the spell (escape).<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179">Loadstone Profile</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649">Thaumaturge Guide</a> <br /> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1229110.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
